          "page_index": 1,
          "confidence": 0.8,
          "backend": "heuristic",
          "text_content": "where d h is the per-head dimension. In practice, inference consists of a prefilling phase that computes KV states for an input context of length L in a single forward pass, followed by an iterative decoding phase that appends one new KV pair per generated token. In long-context question answering, where the generated answer is short, inference cost is often dominated by the prefilling stage.",
