            "y1": 614.6156616210938
          },
          "page_index": 1,
          "confidence": 0.8,
          "backend": "heuristic",
          "text_content": "k ℓ t = W ℓ K h ℓ t , v ℓ t = W ℓ V h ℓ t , (1)",
          "source_block_ids": [
            "086099d2a571"
          ]
        },
        {
          "region_id": "e241fdf96af0",
          "region_class": "paragraph",
          "bbox": {
            "x0": 307.44000244140625,
            "y0": 610.2135620117188,
            "x1": 543.0897827148438,
            "y1": 717.8604736328125
          },
          "page_index": 1,
          "confidence": 0.8,
          "backend": "heuristic",
          "text_content": "During chunk-wise prefilling, each chunk is processed inde- pendently to compute its key–value (KV) cache. Within a chunk C i , positional indices are assigned locally: tokens are indexed from 0 to | C i | − 1 according to their order inside the chunk, regardless of their absolute position in the full input. Keys and queries are then computed using RoPE based on these chunk-local positions, and the resulting KV states are stored in the cache associated with C i . As a result, chunk-wise prefilling encodes KV states under chunk-local",
          "source_block_ids": [
            "77ab0d4ca03e"
          ]
        },
        {
          "region_id": "8feaf570ed68",
          "region_class": "paragraph",
          "bbox": {
