            "y1": 499.4725036621094
          },
          "page_index": 2,
          "confidence": 0.8,
          "backend": "heuristic",
          "text_content": "To further understand why our selection strategy facilitates effective information propagation, we analyze the RoPE similarity between prompt tokens and the selected context tokens. Importantly, this analysis blocks the contribution of token semantics: similarities are computed purely from the RoPE embedding matrices. Specifically, we measure the similarity between the RoPE embeddings of prompt tokens and those of the selected context tokens, and report both the Mean-of-Max (MoM) similarity and the maximum similarity across selected tokens. Higher values indicate that selected tokens occupy RoPE frequency bands that are more closely aligned with the prompt, and are therefore more positionally reachable under causal decoding.",
          "source_block_ids": [
            "ada325fabfce"
          ]
        },
        {
